<div type="definition">
<p>MOVE UP.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The most current general word for rising or raising oneself up, or rising to an upright position of any kind is qǐ 起 (ant. jiàng 降 "go down").</p>
<p>2. Shēng 升 (ant. xià 下 "go down") refers specifically to the rising of something to a higher level, and these levels can be but do not have to be the ranks of a hierarchy.</p>
<p>3. Jìn 進 (ant. tuì 退 "be demoted") refers specifically to the rising in the ranks of a hierarchy.</p>
<p>4. Jìn 晉 is a very formal term referring to the rising of something in the ranks of a hierarchy.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
